Wimbledon continue fine home run

Lyle Taylor showed exactly why Neal Ardley worked so hard to bring him to the club with a superb opener and a man of the match performance today.

Taylor (pictured striking the first goal above) struck his first league goal for the club in style and Rigg sealed it in injury-time to earn a 2-0 win for Wimbledon. The final whistle meant that Wimbledon had made it three wins out of the last four home league matches
